<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-869-768  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 869 768.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  Dec 1989 v6 n12 p219(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Accu-Weather Forecaster. (Software Review) (Metacomet'sweather-forecasting program for the Apple Macintosh) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Smith, Donald Matthew.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Metacomet's $89 Accu-Weather Forecaster lets any Macintosh userwith a modem download and interpret data from over 1,000weather-reporting stations via the National Weather Service'sAccu-Data online database.andP;  The user defines a request and logs onto Accu-Data; Accu-Weather auto-dials the database inPennsylvania, logs on, downloads the requested data and convertsit into text and graphics.andP;  The program archives downloaded dataonce offline; it has commands for overlaying graphicrepresentations of weather data, drawing low-resolution maps forthe entire US or any region, and defining specific data requests.andO;The Save Screen command is not compatible with MultiFinder, andforecasting on the West Coast is more difficult than on the EastCoast because most weather travels from west to east.andO;Accu-Weather Forecaster is nevertheless informative and useful.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Metacomet Software Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Accu-Weather Forecaster (Computer program).andO;Topic:     SimulationDownloadingOn-LineNational Weather ServiceEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>